{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QJx5AsFkdTzW5KTAYawgMn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The ETL pipeline completed successfully. Here's the full summary:\n\n---\n\n## Diagnosis & Fix Summary\n\n### Root Cause\n**Data skew in Stage 3 GROUP BY user_id:**\n- 100,000 total records across 1,000 distinct user IDs\n- user_id=999 holds **50,000 records (50%)** — a **500x skew ratio**\n- With only 256MB executor memory, the single executor handling user_id=999's partition triggered `OutOfMemoryError`\n\n### Fix Applied (combined Option B + C)\nUpdated `etl-job.yaml` with two changes:\n1. **Executor memory raised to 1g** (`spark.executor.memory=1g`) — gives each executor enough headroom\n2. **AQE with skewJoin enabled** (`spark.sql.adaptive.enabled=true` + `spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled=true`) — Spark automatically detects and splits oversized partitions at runtime, preventing hot-key overload\n\n### Verification\n- Job status: **Complete (1/1)** in 85 seconds\n- All 500 tasks finished; log ends with `spark_etl_pipeline_verified`\n- No OOM errors"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2483,"cache_read_input_tokens":35088,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2483},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1dd8616c-d302-44be-86ff-7f89daa15efe","uuid":"bd8dfc58-6114-4993-ae1c-71bc53c77121","request_id":"req_011CcQ5NFq57v1zaWKwbXwRS"}
